          {
            "title": "Question: Why Accessibility?",
            "id": 116250,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Why should we write accessible code?</p><selection iscode=\"false\" multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"4\" correct=\"true\">Both options</item><item value=\"4\" correct=\"false\">To make web pages accessible for everyone, including people with disabilities</item><item value=\"5\" correct=\"false\">To provide users with a meaningful way to navigate and interact with your website</item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Both options.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Question: How are web pages accessible?",
            "id": 116281,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>How can we make code more accessible?</p><selection iscode=\"false\" multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\">By coding HTML in a semantic manner</item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\">By ignoring non-mandatory attributes like <code>alt</code></item><item value=\"3\" correct=\"false\">By designing the website based on the user experience of general users</item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\">By coding HTML in a semantic manner.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Question: <header>,<nav>,<footer>,etc",
            "id": 116287,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Why should we use elements like <code>&lt;header&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;nav&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;footer&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;main&gt;</code>, etc?</p><selection iscode=\"false\" multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\">So that users using a screen reader can jump to sections of a web page</item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\">Because otherwise the webpage won't work</item><item value=\"3\" correct=\"false\">So that it looks fancy</item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\">So that users using a screen reader can jump to sections of a web page.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Question: Generic elements",
            "id": 116319,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Which of the following is <em>not</em> a generic element?</p><selection iscode=\"false\" multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\"><code>&lt;header&gt;</code></item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\"><code>&lt;div&gt;</code></item><item value=\"3\" correct=\"false\"><code>&lt;span&gt;</code></item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>&lt;header&gt;</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Question: Headings",
            "id": 116291,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>We are trying to keep a page as accessible as possible. Should we have an <code>h2</code> after an <code>h5</code> on the same page section?</p><selection iscode=\"false\" multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\">No, we must keep the heading order</item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\">Yes, we can use headings for styling</item><item value=\"3\" correct=\"false\">No, <code>&lt;h5&gt;</code> comes after <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code></item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\">No, we must keep the heading order.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Question: alert role",
            "id": 117323,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>What is wrong with this code?</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"html\" name=\"index.html\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"&lt;!doctype html&gt;\" class=\"meta\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"&lt;\" /><text value=\"html\" class=\"name\" /><text value=\"&gt;\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"&lt;\" /><text value=\"body\" class=\"name\" /><text value=\"&gt;\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"&lt;\" /><text value=\"div\" class=\"name\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"role\" class=\"attr\" /><text value=\"=\" /><text value=\"alert\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\"&gt;\" /><text value=\"This session will expire in 10 seconds. \" /><text value=\"&lt;/\" /><text value=\"div\" class=\"name\" /><text value=\"&gt;\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"&lt;/\" /><text value=\"body\" class=\"name\" /><text value=\"&gt;\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"&lt;/\" /><text value=\"html\" class=\"name\" /><text value=\"&gt;\" /></content></code><selection iscode=\"false\" multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\">The <code>\"alert\"</code> value should have double quotes </item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\">Nothing, It works for me</item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\">The <code>\"alert\"</code> value should have double quotes .</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Question: aria-hidden",
            "id": 117331,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Does the webpage display two paragraphs in this example?<br /></p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"html\" name=\"index.html\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"&lt;!doctype html&gt;\" class=\"meta\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"&lt;\" /><text value=\"html\" class=\"name\" /><text value=\"&gt;\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"&lt;\" /><text value=\"body\" class=\"name\" /><text value=\"&gt;\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"&lt;\" /><text value=\"p\" class=\"name\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"aria-hidden\" class=\"attr\" /><text value=\"&gt;\" /><text value=\"Music Festival\" /><text value=\"&lt;/\" /><text value=\"p\" class=\"name\" /><text value=\"&gt;\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"&lt;\" /><text value=\"p\" class=\"name\" /><text value=\"&gt;\" /><text value=\"Coming Soon\" /><text value=\"&lt;/\" /><text value=\"p\" class=\"name\" /><text value=\"&gt;\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\" \" /><text value=\"&lt;/\" /><text value=\"body\" class=\"name\" /><text value=\"&gt;\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"&lt;/\" /><text value=\"html\" class=\"name\" /><text value=\"&gt;\" /></content></code><selection iscode=\"false\" multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\">Yes, because the attribute hides content only to screen readers</item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\">No, it won't display <code>\"Music Festival\"</code></item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Yes, because the attribute hides content only to screen readers.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
